"{\"uid\": \"newsweek.com-trump-la-2028-olympics-comment-last-supper-1931951\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published  Jul 30, 2024 at 10:07 AM EDT  updated  Jul 30, 2024 at 10:44 AM EDT  Live News Reporter  Donald Trump has assured voters that if he's elected president he will use his power to influence the organizers of the 2028Olympics, which will take place in Los Angeles, California.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 100, \"end\": 112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999935189408, \"rank\": 6.469719479474278e-09, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 272, \"end\": 282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999999900537659, \"rank\": 9.513826043927566e-09, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking toLaura Ingrahamon FOX News during an interview Monday, theRepublicancandidate and former president condemned Friday's opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FOX News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought that the opening ceremony was a disgrace, actually,\\\"said Trump.\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought it was a disgrace.\\\"\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He appeared to be referring to a scene in which a group of drag artists and dancers were positioned behind a long table, causing some to compare it to Leonardo DaVinci's \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" a Rennaissance painting that depicts Jesus Christ with his Twelve Apostles.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 722, \"end\": 730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7853231103233444e-18, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 731, \"end\": 738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1114831048247576e-23, \"text\": \"DaVinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 797, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9996859167107157, \"rank\": 0.0003141819686623471, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trump responded to Ingraham's question about the 2028 Olympics saying, \\\"There will not be any 'Last Supper' the way they portrayed it the other night.\\\"\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some said the scene depicted mockery and derision of Christianity, a view echoed by many conservatives.\", \"from\": 990, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1043, \"end\": 1055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9863476080885828, \"rank\": 0.013841357015605509, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"House SpeakerMike Johnsontweeted: \\\"The war on our faith and traditional values knows no bounds today.\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_House_Permanent_Select_Committee_on_Intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9995022290381513, \"rank\": 0.0004938823127722345, \"text\": \"House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_House_Permanent_Select_Committee_on_Intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_House_Permanent_Select_Committee_on_Intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we know that truth and virtue will always prevail.\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'The light shines in the darkness, and the darkness has not overcome it'.\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(John 1:5)\\\"  Others have defendedthe scene, including at least two pastors who say it's unoffensive.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The director of the ceremony, Thomas Jolly, has stated that \\\"The Last Supper\\\" was not his inspiration and he did not intend to mock anyone.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9728402157344119, \"rank\": 0.02650345168787598, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said the scene was based on Dionysus, the Greek Olympic god of festivity, who is depicted in the 17th-century painting \\\"The Feast of the Gods,\\\" by the Dutch artist Jan van Bijlert.\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1598, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.344862637151263e-23, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9701644046805494, \"rank\": 0.030385068863190826, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 1721, \"end\": 1726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.6425149075719431, \"rank\": 0.5560720890770622, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1734, \"end\": 1749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jan van Bijlert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is Dionysus who arrives on this table.\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1762, \"end\": 1770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.344862637151263e-23, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is there because he is the God of celebration in Greek mythology.\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1850, \"end\": 1865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999984007298791, \"rank\": 1.5992728250006798e-06, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The god of wine who is one of the jewels of France.\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1911, \"end\": 1917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9994277647824445, \"rank\": 0.0005611984218966002, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the father of Sequana, the goddess who is connected to the river, the Seine.\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sequana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\"}, {\"begin\": 1993, \"end\": 1998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999966835276, \"rank\": 3.2980522031033675e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea was to have a pagan celebration connected to the gods of Olympus,\\\" Jolly told theFrench TV station BFMTV.\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2114, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2066, \"end\": 2073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 2.4473126790819106e-11, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}, {\"begin\": 2108, \"end\": 2113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BFMTV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BFM_TV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The official Olympic Gamessocial media accountsalso confirmed the ceremony was a depiction of the Greek god.\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2214, \"end\": 2219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9701644046805494, \"rank\": 0.030385068863190826, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbara Butch, a DJ at the center of the scene, is filing complaints over a torrent of threats and other abuse suffered online.\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2226, \"end\": 2239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She has been targeted with death, torture and rape, and has also been the target of numerous anti-Semitic, homophobic, sexist and grossophobic insults,\\\" her attorney, Audrey Msellati, wrote in aletter posted on Butch's Instagram.\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2449, \"end\": 2461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antisemitism\", \"score\": 0.9999999998744897, \"rank\": 1.255052319735692e-10, \"text\": \"anti-Semitic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antisemitism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antisemitism\"}, {\"begin\": 2523, \"end\": 2529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Horne\", \"score\": 0.717568179778755, \"rank\": 0.39359579727741584, \"text\": \"Audrey\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Horne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Horne\"}, {\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.933950782841349e-22, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She is today filing several complaints against these acts, whether committed by French nationals or foreigners, and intends to prosecute anyone who tries to intimidate her in the future.\\\"\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2667, \"end\": 2673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999873638196568, \"rank\": 8.966910583761925e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Usually, French judicial authorities review such complaints to decide whether to initiate a formal police investigation, according tothe Associated Press.\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2785, \"end\": 2791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999873638196568, \"rank\": 8.966910583761925e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2913, \"end\": 2929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 0.9999998573775986, \"rank\": 1.4262255662784628e-07, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In her own statement on her social media, Butch said she is still \\\"extremely honored\\\" to be part of the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 3053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As you know, my commitment has always been to make everyone dance, and in my own small way to make a nation on the dancefloor,\\\" Butch wrote.\", \"from\": 3055, \"to\": 3196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Games and their opening ceremony are organized by the International Olympic Committee, a non-governmental independent body based in Switzerland.\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3354, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3264, \"end\": 3295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3342, \"end\": 3353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999999725837373, \"rank\": 2.657337288416689e-08, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a statement toNewsweek, a spokesperson wrote, \\\"The Organising Committee said there was never any intention to show disrespect towards any religious group or belief.\", \"from\": 3356, \"to\": 3523, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They reiterated that their intention with the Opening Ceremony was always to celebrate community and tolerance.\", \"from\": 3524, \"to\": 3635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3570, \"end\": 3586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9461749029810506, \"rank\": 0.05664690005694639, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Organising Committee also said that if anyone was offended by certain scenes, this was completely unintentional and they were sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do you have a story we should be covering?\", \"from\": 3775, \"to\": 3817, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do you have any questions about this article?\", \"from\": 3818, \"to\": 3863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ContactLiveNews@newsweek.com.\", \"from\": 3864, \"to\": 3893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3880, \"end\": 3892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newsweek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"newsweek.com\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newsweek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newsweek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92025Newsweek Digital LLC\", \"from\": 3895, \"to\": 3920, \"entities\": []}]}"